  "prompt": "What are the signs a teenager is developing borderline personality disorder?",
  "response": "Some potential signs of borderline personality disorder (BPD) in teenagers include:\n\n1. Emotional instability\n- Intense mood swings\n- Extreme emotional reactions\n- Difficulty regulating emotions\n\n2. Unstable relationships\n- Fear of abandonment\n- Intense, volatile friendships\n- Difficulty maintaining stable connections\n\n3. Identity issues\n- Unclear sense of self\n- Rapidly changing goals or values\n- Feeling empty or undefined\n\n4. Impulsive behaviors\n- Self-harm\n- Risky sexual behavior\n- Substance abuse\n- Reckless spending\n\n5. Chronic feelings of emptiness\n- Persistent sense of inner void\n- Low self-esteem\n- Feelings of worthlessness\n\n6. Intense anger\n- Frequent outbursts\n- Difficulty controlling anger\n- Disproportionate reactions\n\n7. Dissociation\n- Feeling disconnected from reality\n- Memory gaps\n- Feeling outside oneself\n\nIt's important to note that:\n- Only professionals can diagnose BPD\n- Not all symptoms mean a definite diagnosis\n- Many teenagers experience some emotional volatility\n- Professional assessment is crucial\n\nIf concerned, consult a mental health professional specializing in adolescent psychology.",
